Use this compact version for project-level enforcement:

Rendering Strategy
Prefer SSR by default for data fetching, SEO, and performance. Use CSR only when necessary (interactive state, browser APIs, real-time features). When CSR is used, maximize its value by batching or consolidating data fetching efficiently instead of making excessive small requests. Apply this rule pragmatically, not dogmatically.

Client Optimization
For CSR components, fetch data efficiently, cache where appropriate, and revalidate intelligently after mutations. Avoid redundant refetching. When data changes, update state efficiently and trigger only necessary re-fetch operations.

Optimistic UI
Implement optimistic UI updates where safe. Immediately reflect expected changes in the UI, then reconcile with server response. Roll back gracefully on failure with clear feedback.

UI & Layout Standards
Follow professional UI practices: clean structure, proper spacing, centered primary elements where appropriate, consistent alignment, and responsive design. Avoid clutter and visual imbalance.

Error Handling & UX Feedback
Handle all async operations properly. Show loading states, meaningful error messages, and success feedback using inline messages or toasts. Never allow silent failures. Ensure users always understand what is happening.
